Your first job is to marinate the chicken. The longer the better is the rule with marinating! In a #bowl{}, mix the @British chicken thighs{4} with the @chermoula spice mix{1}, @Greek style natural yoghurt{1/2}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @black pepper{good grind}. Make sure the chicken is well coated and put back in the fridge.

Peel and cut the @onion{1/2}(peeled and chopped into ½cm chunks) in half through the root. Chop the top and bottom off the @courgette{1} and cut in half lengthways. Cut each half into three long strips and then chop at 1cm intervals to create small chunks. Peel the @garlic clove{1} and chop finely (use a #garlic press{} if you have one!). Tear off the leaves from the @coriander{5}(leaves torn off and stalks chopped as small as you can). Keep the leaves for later.

Heat a #saucepan{} over medium heat and add @oil{1%tbsp}. Cook the onion for ~{5%minutes} or until softened. Add the chopped garlic, coriander stalks and the courgette. Season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @black pepper{good grind}. Stir in the @basmati rice{1} and make sure the rice is coated with all the flavours in the pan.

Pour in @cold water{350%ml} with the @chicken stock pot{1} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, reduce the heat to a simmer, put a #lid{} on the #pan{} and cook for ~{10%minutes}. Finish the rice dish by removing the pan from the heat (lid still on!) and leave to continue cooking in its own steam, for a further ~{10%minutes}.

As the rice cooks, pre-heat your #grill{} to its highest setting. Put the chicken on a #baking tray{} and cook it for ~{15%minutes}.

> Tip: You want the yogurt marinade to scorch, so don't be tempted to turn the grill down. It's all about flavour!

Turn the chicken after ~{7%minutes} and cook for another ~{7%minutes} or until the centre is no longer pink.

Chop the coriander leaves and zest and juice @lemon{1/2}(zested and juiced) whilst the rice and chicken do their thing. Mix the lemon zest through the remaining @Greek style natural yoghurt{1/2} and keep to one side.

Once the rice is ready, stir in the coriander leaves and half the lemon juice. Taste and add more salt if needed and more lemon if you feel it needs a bit more zing!

Cut the chicken into ½cm strips and serve on top of a bed of rice. Finish with dollops of the lemony yoghurt and enjoy!